__If-Else Statements__
--> Run code if condition is True
    else → Run code if condition is False
    elif → Check additional conditions
--> It uses comparison (==, >, <) and logical operators (and, or, not), Can nest(if-else in another if-else) "if" statements for more complex logic, Can write concise one-line conditions with ternary operators.
***Practise***
1) Write a program that asks for a number and checks if it’s positive, negative, or zero.
num = int(input("Enter a number:"))
if num > 0:
    print("Positive")
elif num < 0:
    print("Negative")
else:
    print("zero")
o/p:- Enter a number = 9
      Positive
